# Security Guardrails (Tier 1 — highest priority)

## Blocked Commands (never suggest or execute)
- `rm -rf`, `rm -r`, `rm -fr` — file destruction
- `git push --force`, `git push -f` — history rewriting
- `git reset --hard` — uncommitted work destruction
- `curl * | bash`, `wget * | bash` — remote code execution
- `DROP TABLE`, `DROP DATABASE`, `TRUNCATE TABLE` — database destruction
- `chmod 777`, `chmod -R 777` — permission escalation

## Required Before git push
```bash
bash core/tests/skills/test-skill-triggering.sh  # must show Result: PASS
bash core/scripts/verify-skills-lock.sh          # must show no drift
```

## Secret Detection
Run before push: `bash core/skills/leak-check/` pattern or gitleaks.
Never commit .env files with real values.

## Command Wrapper
Route risky commands through: `bash core/scripts/safe-run.sh "<command>"`
